â­ï¸â­ï¸â­ï¸â­ï¸/5
.
I have a desert heart.
.
Iâ€™ve always felt most at home in the panoramic desolation of the American Southwest. When I lived in California I constantly sought out ways to immerse myself in those sweeping expanses of nothingness. And there was a part of me that felt a deep, almost elemental attraction to the idea of simply disappearing, of packing up, cutting ties, & pulling a Chris McCandless.
.
It makes sense, then, that The Bright Lands â€“ a book that flirts with trying to do too much & succeeds anyway â€“ would speak to me powerfully. Never mind the fact that it also dabbles in nostalgia (which I have a weakness for), murder mysteries (which I love), & high school football (which I find oddly compelling despite not caring a bit about the game itself). But most importantly itâ€™s the vast desert outside the small Texas town where the book is set that resonates the most. Named the Flats, itâ€™s a place of secrets, where unspeakable crimes can & have happened, & where the bookâ€™s main characters must continually return to discover the truth of the sickness that plagues the town.
.
Joel Whitley fled Bentley, TX, shortly after high school. A gay man persecuted by peers & adults alike, he knew heâ€™d have more of a life in New York City. Now, ten years later, he returns to help his younger brother Dylan, a high school football phenom, break out of Bentleyâ€™s confines, too.
.
And then Dylan disappears.
.
Aided by his former girlfriend Starsha Clark â€“ now a Bentley police officer â€“ Joel tries to locate his brother while simultaneously untangling the dark secret at Bentleyâ€™s core. 
.
No one could accuse author John Fram of not being ambitious. It is, as I mentioned earlier, a book that does so much it could have belly flopped spectacularly. The meth trade, the twisted rituals of Bentleyâ€™s football team, a pastor with a secret, high school bullies, the necessity of leaving your hometown despite the hold it has on you, & a distinctly Lovecraftian finale â€“ Fram tackles all these things & more. Itâ€™s a murder mystery, a meditation on home, & a cosmic horror story.
.
It shouldnâ€™t have worked.
.
But boy howdy did it.";}i:238;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:239;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:4;}i:240;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEudp2hgZUu";}i:241;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:258:"https://scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/s1080x1080/118937318_954633215010792_750073407584945398_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=100&_nc_ohc=4fmrXTJ2ShEAX-vw87m&_nc_tp=15&oh=c10c39b80d430ada3973ed3054c79662&oe=5F7A8C9E";}i:242;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:243;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:29162814766;}i:244;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:245;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:246;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:247;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2390978826812028980";}i:248;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEudpM1nHg0";}i:249;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599246908;}i:250;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:491:"Happy Friday.. sprinkle some inspiration in your day.

